# Testing rules — {{project_name}}

## Requirements
- Every bug fix includes a failing test reproducing the bug before the fix — no exceptions
- Tests live next to the code they test
- No mocking the database in integration tests; use a real test database
- Test names describe observable behavior, not implementation

## What to test
- Happy path, boundary conditions, expected failure modes, integration with real dependencies

## What not to test
- Framework internals, implementation details the type system rules out

## CI
- Every PR passes the full test suite before merge
- Flaky tests are bugs: fix or delete, never skip

